# scitex-genai — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env` (or export inline) and fill the values your workflow
# actually needs. Most knobs have safe defaults; only set the ones you
# want to override.
#
# Cloud-provider API keys are NOT listed here on purpose — they are
# read from the standard provider-canonical env vars (e.g.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, GOOGLE_API_KEY) which already
# have ecosystem-wide conventions outside scitex-genai's surface.
#
# The vars below are scitex-genai-specific (`SCITEX_GENAI_*`) and
# control routing / endpoint discovery for the LOCAL vLLM provider.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# vLLM — OpenAI-compatible local server (provider="vLLM" in _PARAMS.py)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Base URL of the running vLLM server. Defaults to the local loopback
# port that `vllm serve --port 8765` uses. Override for a remote box or
# a custom port. Must end in `/v1` (the OpenAI API root).
# SCITEX_GENAI_VLLM_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8765/v1

# API key sent in the `Authorization` header. vLLM IGNORES the value by
# default, but the OpenAI Python SDK rejects empty strings — when this
# env var is unset, scitex-genai substitutes the placeholder "EMPTY".
# Set this only if your vLLM instance is behind a reverse proxy /
# gateway that enforces a token.
# SCITEX_GENAI_VLLM_API_KEY=
